id: pm-5mua
title: Expose runtime command-path state in extension explore
description: GitHub issue #27 reported that a project extension could appear active in extension explore while its registered command path was unavailable. Extension explore should surface runtime activation state and registered command paths so agents can trust the lifecycle output.
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[4]: agent-ux,extensions,github,pm-cli
created_at: "2026-05-12T22:05:12.311Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-22T19:18:07.912Z"
author: codex-audit
acceptance_criteria: pm extension/package explore reports runtime_active/activation_status plus command paths for enabled extensions; extension-defined paths such as pm-graph export remain invocable; regression tests cover the behavior; GitHub issue #27 is addressed.
parent: pm-rnpb
resolution: Fixed
expected_result: extension/package explore exposes runtime status and registered command paths for enabled extensions
actual_result: "runtime_active/activation_status plus command_paths/action_paths are present, and pm-graph export regression passes"
comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-12T22:05:12.311Z",codex-audit,"Duplicate check before create: pm search pm-graph command path active extension github issue 27 --limit 10 found only closed historical extension lifecycle items and no open issue for this GitHub report."
  "2026-05-12T22:08:35.749Z",codex-audit,"Evidence: implemented runtime probing for extension/package explore, added command_paths/action_paths to extension summaries, and verified a pm-graph export dynamic command path remains invocable. Verification passed: linked focused suite (112 tests), full release gates (1289 tests, 100% coverage, static/docs/secret/pack/compatibility), pm health/vectorization ok with only known history drift warnings."
  "2026-07-22T19:18:07.912Z",codex-sdk-boundary-20260722,"GitHub provenance: added the missing direct pm item link to closed GH-27 for runtime extension command-path exposure."
